    <text id="A0581T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Cochran provides a general update on camp life and apologizes to his mother for
                    buying a pistol. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mother</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-05-30">May the 30 1861 </date>
                        <name type="place">Harpers Ferry </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Mother </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter of the 23<hi rend="super">d</hi> came to hand. I am very sorry that I
                    bought a <orig reg="pistol">pistole</orig> but I was <orig reg="forced"
                    >forsed</orig> to buy one because I had to go on picket <orig reg="guard"
                    >gard</orig> and the men on picket. When two were resting one was going and they
                    have at night riding by bushes have been fired <orig reg="upon">uppon</orig> by
                    an unseen foe last night the officer of the night whilst going the rounds was
                    fired at but not hurt.</p>

                <p>The things that are not in the <orig reg="pistol">pistole</orig> case I took <add
                        hand="h1" place="inline">out</add> the <orig reg="provision">provison</orig>
                    that you were going to send down. you can send it to the <abbr
                        expan="Harper's Ferry">
                        <orig reg="Ferry">fery</orig>
                    </abbr> and I wish you would get me some coloured stuff and make me two shirts
                    and pack them in the box with the <orig reg="provision">provison</orig>. <orig
                        reg="also">all so</orig> send me one of little cans of powder that Johnie
                    sent sent me from Richmond.</p>

                <p>You ask me if I want more <orig reg="clothes">clotes</orig> I want none but what
                    I have mentioned above. </p>

                <p>I am now very well and on duty <orig reg="today">to day</orig> camp life is right
                    hard but I do not mind it.</p>

                <p>I have tended to my horse very well and he stands it as well if not better than
                    any other horse in camp. </p>

                <p>There is no <orig reg="news">knewse</orig> here at all you <orig reg="hear"
                    >here</orig> more <orig reg="news">knewse</orig> than we do. I am very well and
                    hope to <orig reg="find">finde</orig> you the same</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your Affectionate Son </salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="Benjamin Franklin">B.F.</abbr> Cochran </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
